            {
                "name": "Been",
                "url": "/topics/been"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_d_burns_618077",
        "quote": "Every time you feel depressed about something, try to identify a corresponding negative thought you had just prior to and during the depression. Because these thoughts have actually created your bad mood, by learning to restructure them, you can change your mood.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David D. Burns",
            "url": "/quotes/david_d_burns_618077"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Thought",
                "url": "/topics/thought"
            },
            {
                "name": "Bad",
                "url": "/topics/bad"
            },
            {
                "name": "Mood",
                "url": "/topics/mood"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_d_burns_618078",
        "quote": "A poor self-image is the magnifying glass that can transform a trivial mistake or an imperfection into an overwhelming symbol of personal defeat.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David D. Burns",
            "url": "/quotes/david_d_burns_618078"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Mistake",
                "url": "/topics/mistake"
            },
            {
                "name": "Glass",
                "url": "/topics/glass"
            },
            {
                "name": "Symbol",
                "url": "/topics/symbol"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_d_burns_618070",
        "quote": "Cognitive therapy is a fast-acting technology of mood modification that you can learn to apply on your own. It can help you eliminate the symptoms and experience personal growth so you can minimize future upsets and cope with depression more effectively in the future.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David D. Burns",
            "url": "/quotes/david_d_burns_618070"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Mood",
                "url": "/topics/mood"
            },
            {
                "name": "Own",
                "url": "/topics/own"
            },
            {
                "name": "Eliminate",
                "url": "/topics/eliminate"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_d_burns_618079",
        "quote": "Negative thinking patterns can be immensely deceptive and persuasive, and change is rarely easy. But with patience and persistence, I believe that nearly all individuals suffering from depression can improve and experience a sense of joy and self-esteem once again.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David D. Burns",
            "url": "/quotes/david_d_burns_618079"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Self-Esteem",
                "url": "/topics/self-esteem"
            },
            {
                "name": "Persuasive",
                "url": "/topics/persuasive"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_d_burns_618066",
        "quote": "People who are prone to anxiety are nearly always people-pleasers who fear conflict and negative feelings like anger. When you feel upset, you sweep your problems under the rug because you don't want to upset anyone. You do this so quickly and automatically that you're not even aware you're doing it.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David D. Burns",
            "url": "/quotes/david_d_burns_618066"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Doing",
                "url": "/topics/doing"
            },
            {
                "name": "Upset",
                "url": "/topics/upset"
            },
            {
                "name": "Rug",
                "url": "/topics/rug"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_d_burns_201467",
        "quote": "Depression can seem worse than terminal cancer, because most cancer patients feel loved and they have hope and self-esteem.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David D. Burns",
            "url": "/quotes/david_d_burns_201467"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Self-Esteem",
                "url": "/topics/self-esteem"
            },
            {
                "name": "Feel",
                "url": "/topics/feel"
            },
            {
                "name": "Patients",
                "url": "/topics/patients"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_d_burns_618063",
        "quote": "Practically everybody knows what it's like to feel anxious, worried, nervous, afraid, uptight, or panicky. Often, anxiety is just a nuisance, but sometimes it can cripple you and prevent you from doing what you really want with your life. But I have some great news for you: You can change the way you feel.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David D. Burns",
            "url": "/quotes/david_d_burns_618063"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Doing",
                "url": "/topics/doing"
            },
            {
                "name": "Everybody",
                "url": "/topics/everybody"
            },
            {
                "name": "Some",
                "url": "/topics/some"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_d_burns_201468",
        "quote": "Perfectionism becomes a badge of honor with you playing the part of the suffering hero.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David D. Burns",
            "url": "/quotes/david_d_burns_201468"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Suffering",
                "url": "/topics/suffering"
            },
            {
                "name": "Honor",
                "url": "/topics/honor"
            },
            {
                "name": "Badge",
                "url": "/topics/badge"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_d_burns_618068",
        "quote": "Depression has been called the world's number one public health problem. In fact, depression is so widespread it is considered the common cold of psychiatric disturbances. But there is a grim difference between depression and a cold. Depression can kill you.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David D. Burns",
            "url": "/quotes/david_d_burns_618068"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Fact",
                "url": "/topics/fact"
            },
            {
                "name": "Been",
                "url": "/topics/been"
            },
            {
                "name": "Considered",
                "url": "/topics/considered"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_d_burns_618071",
        "quote": "The first principle of cognitive therapy is that all your moods are created by your 'cognitions,' or thoughts. A cognition refers to the way you look at things - your perceptions, mental attitudes, and beliefs. It includes the way you interpret things - what you say. about something or someone to yourself.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David D. Burns",
            "url": "/quotes/david_d_burns_618071"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Principle",
                "url": "/topics/principle"
            },
            {
                "name": "About",
                "url": "/topics/about"
            },
            {
                "name": "Attitudes",
                "url": "/topics/attitudes"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_d_burns_539326",
        "quote": "Therapy is not to 'talk about' things, but to change the person's life, and to relieve suffering, such as depression, anxiety, or relationship problems.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David D. Burns",
            "url": "/quotes/david_d_burns_539326"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Change",
                "url": "/topics/change"
            },
            {
                "name": "Suffering",
                "url": "/topics/suffering"
            },
            {
                "name": "Therapy",
                "url": "/topics/therapy"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_d_burns_618067",
        "quote": "The stereotype of psychotherapy portrayed in popular books and movies is lying on the couch and saying whatever comes into your mind, while a kindly psychoanalyst listens and nods knowingly from time to time. After years and years, something wonderful is supposed to happen.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David D. Burns",
            "url": "/quotes/david_d_burns_618067"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Couch",
                "url": "/topics/couch"
            },
            {
                "name": "Your",
                "url": "/topics/your"
            },
            {
                "name": "Years And Years",
                "url": "/topics/years_and_years"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_d_burns_618061",
        "quote": "There is no 'ultimate goal of therapy.' Thinking there is some ultimate or universal goal of therapy is one of the most fundamental errors of our field. To me, that concept is rather arrogant, as if therapists were some kind of spiritual experts who knew what human beings are supposed to be like.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David D. Burns",
            "url": "/quotes/david_d_burns_618061"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Some",
                "url": "/topics/some"
            },
            {
                "name": "Rather",
                "url": "/topics/rather"
            },
            {
                "name": "Concept",
                "url": "/topics/concept"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_d_burns_618080",
        "quote": "I always wanted to see people's lives transformed from depression and anxiety to joy and peace.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David D. Burns",
            "url": "/quotes/david_d_burns_618080"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Anxiety",
                "url": "/topics/anxiety"
            },
            {
                "name": "Always",
                "url": "/topics/always"
            },
            {
                "name": "See",
                "url": "/topics/see"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/david_d_burns_201465",
        "quote": "That's one of the peculiar things about bad moods - we often fool ourselves and create misery by telling ourselves things that simply are not true.",
        "author": {
            "name": "David D. Burns",
            "url": "/quotes/david_d_burns_201465"
        },
        "topics": [
